The paper deals with coding theory and error-correction, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The use of cyclic and constacyclic codes suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The analysis of linear fractional transformations and the algorithmic approach to constructing MDS symbol-pair codes suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the Signal and Image Processing (cs.SI) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories.
